name: Gaza - Breathable Nail Polish
description: This olive green is inspired by the city Gaza, Palestine. The city of Gaza [gah-zuh] has been continuously inhabited for more than 3,000 years and was a crossroads of ancient civilizations. This green is inspired directly from the Palestinian olive trees, a major agricultural crop of the country as well as the symbol of nationality and connection to the land.

name: Dakar - Breathable Nail Polish
description: This pretty light pink nail polish is inspired by Dakar, Senegal [dah-kahr] and it’s pink Lake Retba, also fondly called “Lac Rose” or “Lake Rose”. The lake gets its pink hue from an algae that produces a red pigment, and is at its most vivid during the dry seasons. It’s currently under consideration as a World Heritage Site by UNESCO.

name: Beirut - Breathable Nail Polish
description: This warm nude pink color was inspired by the beautiful and fascinating Lebanese city of Beirut. One of the oldest cities in the world, Beirut is known for its rich history, its beautiful coast, and its vibrant culture - even being called the "Paris of the East." This amazing city is home to Byzantine Mosaics, extravagant mosques and cathedrals, roman baths, ancient streets, and ruins from the Canaanite and Ottoman eras. One of the famous landmarks off the coast of Beirut, Pigeon's Rock, is known to have been the site of some of the oldest evidence of human existence was found. It is also claimed to be the remains of the sea monster the green hero Perseus killed to save Andromeda, having used Medusa's head to turn the monster into stone.

name: Java - Breathable Nail Polish
description: This opaque black was inspired by the black panthers, or melanistic leopards, found on the Indonesian island of Java. Java is the 13th largest island in the world and formed mostly as a result of volcanic eruptions.

name: Komodo - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This pink is inspired by the Indonesian island, Puluo Komodo. Home to over 4,000 Komodo dragons, volcanic hills, savannahs, forests, and Pantai Merah-The Pink Beach. This beach gets its striking color from microscopic single-celled organisms called foraminifera, which produce a red pigment on the coral reefs. This mixed with the white sands give the waters a stunning pink color that the island is famous for.

Komodo is an elegant, light amaranth pink nail polish. Komodo is lighter and less bold than Nizwa.

name: Nizwa - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
Nizwa is inspired by the beautifully fragrant rose gardens of Oman's Jebel Akhdar, or "green mountain" which is located in the city of Nizwa. Every spring, these gardens are filled with vibrant pink roses that are transformed into the famous Omani rose water. This rose water is used for celebratory, culinary or medicinal purposes.

Nizwa (niz-wah) is best described as a bold, bubblegum pink shade.

name: Isfahan - Breathable Nail Polish

Isfahan [is-fuh-hahn] is a soft mauve cream. It is a deeper and slightly warmer version of our best-seller, Kashmir.

name: Goychay - Breathable Nail Polish
description: Goychay [goe-shay] is inspired by the Azerbaijani city famous for its pomegranate growing industry and its pomegranate festival. This annual cultural festival features a parade with traditional Azerbaijani dances and music, a marketplace with craftsmen and artists displaying their work, and of course an exhibition of all the different pomegranate dishes and products.

name: Cusco - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This deep mauve pink is inspired by the stunning rainbow mountain of Cusco, Peru. Known as Vinicunca, or the mountain of seven colors, the mountain is considered a holy site in Peru. Cusco is the former capital city of the Incas, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and the oldest continuously inhabited city in the Americas.

Cusco is a deep mauve pink cream. Cusco is darker and cooler than Jaipur and less bright compared to Monduli.

name: Aswan - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
Aswan [as-wahn] is inspired by the historical and awe-inspiring city of Aswan, Egypt. In Aswan you will find Abu Simbel, incredible massive rock temples that were built by Ramesses II - the Great Temple, dedicated to himself, and the Small Temple, dedicated to his chief wife Queen Nefertari. Other incredible historical monuments are sprinkled throughout Aswan, from the Temple of Philae, Temple of Kom Ombo, Temple of Isis, and even mausoleums from the Fatamid Era.

Aswan is best described as a rich, opaque cocoa brown.

name: Himalayas - Breathable Nail Polish
description: Himalayas [him-uh-ley-uh-z] is inspired by the pink rock salt mined near the Himalayan mountains of Punjab, Pakistan. The Himalayan pink salt is found in the Khewra Salt Mine, one of the oldest and largest salt mines in the world and the salt itself is thought to have been created millions of years ago. This salt mine was discovered by Alexander the Great's troops in 320 BC, and the story is that the sick horses of his troops licked the stone and recovered, leading to the belief held today by many that the salt is loaded with minerals and provide health benefits.

name: Sakura - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
Sakura [saa-kur-uh] is inspired by the stunning pale pink cherry blossoms found in Sakura, Japan. In fact, the most common of all the cherry blossoms are called "Sakura" or Japanese Cherry. Located in Chiba prefecture, Sakura has been inhabited since prehistory and is home to the National Museum of Japanese History. Sakura blossoms are seen as a symbol of renewal, rebirth and new beginnings. Sakura blossoms only bloom for a brief time - best viewed during Spring time in Japan.

Sakura is best described as a muted pink nude, nearly opaque with two coats.

name: Tuscany - Breathable Nail Polish
description:

Tuscany is a burnt sienna halal nail polish color with red undertone.

name: Kabul - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This light brown nude is inspired by Kabul, Afghanistan - a city that has existed for over 3,500 years. The city is situated in a valley between the Hindu Kush mountains and has a rich history, from being a part of the Achaemenid Empire to being a key location of the Silk Road to seeing both British and Soviet rule. The city continues to develop and is known for its beautiful gardens, palaces, and mosques.

Kabul [ke-bool] is a light brown nude color, perfect for everyday wear.
